# Testing Standards

- Map tests to requirement IDs where possible (FR/NFR/UAT references in test names or comments).
- Prefer deterministic tests: avoid timing flakiness and uncontrolled network dependencies.
- Keep unit tests fast and isolated; mock IO boundaries only.
- Use integration tests for cross-module flows (onboarding, score sync, family join, SOS retry).
- Cover offline and degraded-network scenarios for critical user journeys.

# Quality Gates

- Add tests for bug fixes to prevent regressions.
- Verify edge cases and fallback behavior, not only happy paths.
- For new features, include at least:
  - one unit test for core logic
  - one integration-style behavior check

# Naming and Readability

- Use clear test names: `given_when_then` or behavior-first style.
- Keep arrange/act/assert structure obvious.
